docs-site\docs\en\plugins\development.md:472: `status` only accepts `accepted`, `pending`, `completed`, `failed`, or `unsupported`. `message` and `externalReference` are length-limited. `metadata` only keeps flat JSON scalar fields. This contract currently appears only in dispatch responses and extension audit logs for later lifecycle orchestration decisions. It does not directly write instance status, order status, balance, or resource delivery results.
docs-site\docs\en\plugins\development.md:476: Gateway extensions declare third-party payment provider hooks for availability, payment creation, verification, refund, and callback handling. Payments are a high-risk money flow. PayIncus keeps payment creation, active verification, async callbacks, admin sync, and original-channel refunds inside internal state machines. Extension webhooks can only return normalized results; they cannot directly write real balance credit, balance state, or order status.
