docs-site\docs\en\plugins\development.md:860: The consent endpoint `GET /api/oauth-provider/authorize/consent` also returns `scopeMetadata`. Third-party developer docs and frontend/admin UI should not hard-code scope descriptions anymore. `resources` only describes currently covered public resource paths for the scope. It does not mean access to admin APIs, payment callbacks, provider payloads, internal audits, or cross-user data.
